for u, v in G.edges():
    G[u][v]['weight'] = np.random.randint(1, 10)

node_sizes = [G.degree(n) * 300 for n in G.nodes()]

edge_widths = [G[u][v]['weight'] for u, v in G.edges()]

Problem 2-B Implement the Page Rank Algorithm and calculate the number of iterations required to determine the convergence point and Validate the result with the pre-defined page rank function.

In [8]:
def page_rank(G, d=0.85, max_iter=100, tol=1e-6):
    N = len(G)
    P = np.ones(N) / N
    A = nx.to_numpy_array(G)
    outdeg = A.sum(axis=1)

    for i in range(max_iter):
        P_new = np.zeros(N)
        for n in range(N):
            P_new[n] = (1-d)/N + d * sum(P[j]/outdeg[j] for j in range(N) if A[j][n] > 0)
        if np.linalg.norm(P_new-P) < tol:
            print("Converged at iteration:", i)
            break
        P = P_new
    return P

G = nx.karate_club_graph()
pr = page_rank(G)
print("Custom PR:", pr)
print("NetworkX PR:", nx.pagerank(G))

Problem 5 Apply various community detection algorithms on a small real-world network (e.g. Karate club) and plot the communities revealed with different colors. Also, compare the results of these algorithms using any two evaluation measures studied. Show the comparative results using bar plots.

In [16]:
np.random.seed(42)
G = nx.karate_club_graph()

ground_truth = [G.nodes[n]['club'] for n in G.nodes()]
gt_map = {name: i for i, name in enumerate(sorted(set(ground_truth)))}
gt_labels = np.array([gt_map[x] for x in ground_truth])

lp_comm = list(community.label_propagation_communities(G))
def partition_to_labels(partition):
    labels = np.zeros(len(G.nodes()), dtype=int)
    for cid, community_nodes in enumerate(partition):
        for node in community_nodes:
            labels[node] = cid
    return labels

lp_labels = partition_to_labels(lp_comm)

gn_gen = community.girvan_newman(G)
gn_comm = tuple(sorted(c) for c in next(gn_gen)) 
gn_labels = partition_to_labels(gn_comm)

gm_comm = community.greedy_modularity_communities(G)
gm_comm_sets = [set(c) for c in gm_comm]
gm_labels = partition_to_labels(gm_comm_sets)

mod_lp = community.modularity(G, [set(c) for c in lp_comm])
mod_gn = community.modularity(G, [set(c) for c in gn_comm])
mod_gm = community.modularity(G, gm_comm_sets)

nmi_lp = normalized_mutual_info_score(gt_labels, lp_labels)
nmi_gn = normalized_mutual_info_score(gt_labels, gn_labels)
nmi_gm = normalized_mutual_info_score(gt_labels, gm_labels)

algos = ["Label Propagation", "Girvan-Newman", "Greedy Modularity"]
mod_scores = [mod_lp, mod_gn, mod_gm]
nmi_scores = [nmi_lp, nmi_gn, nmi_gm]

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.bar(algos, mod_scores)
plt.ylabel("Modularity")
plt.title("Modularity Comparison")
plt.ylim(0, max(mod_scores)*1.2)
for i,v in enumerate(mod_scores):
    plt.text(i, v+0.01, f"{v:.3f}", ha='center')
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.bar(algos, nmi_scores)
plt.ylabel("NMI (vs ground truth)")
plt.title("NMI Comparison")
plt.ylim(0, 1)
for i,v in enumerate(nmi_scores):
    plt.text(i, v+0.02, f"{v:.3f}", ha='center')
plt.show()

def plot_partition(G, labels, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42) 
    unique_labels = np.unique(labels)
    cmap = plt.cm.get_cmap('tab10', len(unique_labels))
    node_colors = [cmap(label % 10) for label in labels]
    nx.draw_networkx_nodes(G, pos, node_color=node_colors, node_size=300)
    nx.draw_networkx_edges(G, pos, alpha=0.7)
    nx.draw_networkx_labels(G, pos, font_size=8)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

plot_partition(G, lp_labels, "Communities: Label Propagation")
plot_partition(G, gn_labels, "Communities: Girvan-Newman (first split)")
plot_partition(G, gm_labels, "Communities: Greedy Modularity")

Problem 6 Simulate diffusion trends for different epidemic models and present results using appropriate visuals.

In [18]:
beta = 0.3         
gamma = 0.1        
initial_frac = 0.05  
t_max = 100        
n_runs = 200      

def initialize_states(G, initial_frac):
    states = {}
    for node in G.nodes():
        states[node] = 'S'
    k = max(1, int(initial_frac * G.number_of_nodes()))
    infected_nodes = random.sample(list(G.nodes()), k)
    for n in infected_nodes:
        states[n] = 'I'
    return states

def step_SIR(G, states, beta, gamma):
    new_states = states.copy()
    for node in G.nodes():
        if states[node] == 'S':
            for nbr in G.neighbors(node):
                if states[nbr] == 'I':
                    if random.random() < beta:
                        new_states[node] = 'I'
                        break
    for node in G.nodes():
        if states[node] == 'I':
            if random.random() < gamma:
                new_states[node] = 'R'
    return new_states

def step_SIS(G, states, beta, gamma):
    new_states = states.copy()
    for node in G.nodes():
        if states[node] == 'S':
            for nbr in G.neighbors(node):
                if states[nbr] == 'I' and random.random() < beta:
                    new_states[node] = 'I'
                    break
        elif states[node] == 'I':
            if random.random() < gamma:
                new_states[node] = 'S'
    return new_states

def run_simulation(G, model='SIR', beta=0.3, gamma=0.1, initial_frac=0.05, t_max=100):
    states = initialize_states(G, initial_frac)
    S, I, R = [], [], []
    for t in range(t_max):
        counts = {'S':0,'I':0,'R':0}
        for node in G.nodes():
            counts[states[node]] += 1
        S.append(counts['S'])
        I.append(counts['I'])
        R.append(counts['R'])
        if model == 'SIR':
            states = step_SIR(G, states, beta, gamma)
        elif model == 'SIS':
            states = step_SIS(G, states, beta, gamma)
        else:
            raise ValueError("model must be 'SIR' or 'SIS'")
    return np.array(S), np.array(I), np.array(R)

def multiple_runs(G, model, runs, **kwargs):
    results_I = []
    for r in range(runs):
        S,I,R = run_simulation(G, model=model, **kwargs)
        results_I.append(I)
    results_I = np.array(results_I)  # shape (runs, t_max)
    mean_I = results_I.mean(axis=0)
    std_I = results_I.std(axis=0)
    return mean_I, std_I

print("Simulating... (this may take a moment)")
mean_I_sir, std_I_sir = multiple_runs(G, 'SIR', n_runs, beta=beta, gamma=gamma, initial_frac=initial_frac, t_max=t_max)
mean_I_sis, std_I_sis = multiple_runs(G, 'SIS', n_runs, beta=beta, gamma=gamma, initial_frac=initial_frac, t_max=t_max)

N = G.number_of_nodes()
t = np.arange(t_max)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(t, mean_I_sir / N, label='SIR mean infected (fraction)')
plt.fill_between(t, (mean_I_sir - std_I_sir)/N, (mean_I_sir + std_I_sir)/N, alpha=0.2)
plt.xlabel('Time step')
plt.ylabel('Fraction infected')
plt.title(f'SIR epidemic (beta={beta}, gamma={gamma})  averaged over {n_runs} runs')
plt.ylim(0,1)
plt.legend()
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(t, mean_I_sis / N, label='SIS mean infected (fraction)')
plt.fill_between(t, (mean_I_sis - std_I_sis)/N, (mean_I_sis + std_I_sis)/N, alpha=0.2)
plt.xlabel('Time step')
plt.ylabel('Fraction infected')
plt.title(f'SIS epidemic (beta={beta}, gamma={gamma})  averaged over {n_runs} runs')
plt.ylim(0,1)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
